item.description:
arXiv:2507.14950v1 Announce Type: cross 
Abstract: In this paper, we prove that for any $X\subset \R^n$ that is a $d$-dimensional definable set in an o-minimal structure and is Lipschitz regular at any $p\in X$, the following items are equivalent: (i) $C_3(X,p)$ is a $d$-dimensional linear subspace for any $p\in X$, and depends continuously on $p$;
  (ii) $C_4(X,p)=C_3(X,p)$ for any $p\in X$; (iii) $C_4(X,p)$ is a $d$-dimensional linear subspace for any $p\in X$;
  (iv) $C_5(X,p)$ is a $d-$dimensional linear subspace for any $p\in X$; (v) $X$ is $C^1$ smooth.
